FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: AccountNumber
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Identification number of an account.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: AffirmationIndicator
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Used to indicate "yes", "no" statements e.g. Serialized Product.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: AttemptCount
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Indicates whether this message is the first attempt to execute this transaction, or a retry. This element is optional and, when specified, should be an integer 1 or greater. If it is not specified, or is specified and has a value of 1, then this is the first attempt. A value greater than 1 indicates a retry attempt.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: BusinessActivityIdentifier
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: An identifier which specifies a business activity.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: BusinessConstraint
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A constraint that must be met by the entire response document.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: BusinessTaxIdentifier
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Identifying number for Tax Information Field.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: Cardinality
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A number that specifies the upper or lower bound for an object (e.g. product sub-component) in a collection.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: CheckNumber
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: The identifier of a bank cheque.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: CommunicationsNumber
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: The electro-technical communication number, e.g., telephone number, facsimile number, pager number.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: ConfirmationNumber
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: An identifier used to reference the confirmation information that describes the processing of a business action e.g. subscription confirmation.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: CountableAmount
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Dimensionless magnitude, e.g. number of products.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: DateStamp
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Specifies a specific date. Date stamp based on the ISO 8601 specification. The "Z" following the day identifier (DD) is used to indicate Coordinated Universal Time. Informal format: CCYYMMDDZ

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: DateTimeStamp
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Specifies an instance in time. Based on the ISO 8601 specification where "CC" represents the century, "YY" the year, "MM" the month and "DD" the day. The letter "T" is the date/time separator and "hh", "mm", "ss.sss" represent hour, minute and second respectively. This representation is immediately followed by a "Z" to indicate Coordinated Universal Time. Informal format: CCYYMMDDThhmmss.sssZ

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: DigitalCertificateSignature
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A data structure created using public key cryptography and one-way hash functions to produce a signature on the data that can be authenticated and which is difficult to forge or repudiate. A digital signature is also know as an encrypted message digest.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDistributionFormatCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: An electronic resource/asset distribution format.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: EmailAddress
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Electronic mail address.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: NationalExportControlClassificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying product classification for export regulation.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: NationalFederalCommunicationsCommissionLicenseNumberClassificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Product classification according to United States Federal Communications Commission licensing authority.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: NationalFoodAndDrugAdministrationCertificationNumberClassificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Product classification according to United States Food and Drug Administration authority.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: FreeFormText
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Unformatted text.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: FundTransferRoutingNumber
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Bank routing number used for electronic fund transfers.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAccountClassificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Account classification indicating its functionality, e.g., credit card account, debit card account.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAccountProfileResponseCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying whether changes to an account have been resent in their entirety or only the changes have been sent.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAccountTypeCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying whether an account is for customer information or vendor information.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAccountUseCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the purpose of the account.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalActionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the business action that must be performed on or with the data.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAdministeringAuthorityCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the governing body responsible for administering a standard.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalAttachmentDescriptionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the type of product attachment, e.g. assembly instructions, block diagrams, test requirements, etc.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalBilledAmountTypeCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the type of charge being billed, e.g. principal.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalBusinessActionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying a business action. The identifier is found in table 4.2 of the PIP specification document.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalBusinessIdentifier
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A unique business identifier. The DUNS number is specified by RosettaNet.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalBusinessServiceCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying a business service network component. This code is found in table 4.1 in a PIP specification document.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalBusinessSignalCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the business signal message.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalCarrierCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A unique carrier identification code, based on Standard Carrier Alpha Code(s)

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalClaimCostTypeCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the type of product pricing for a claim.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalComponentNameCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the name of a component. This is found in the technical property dictionary.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalCountryCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the two character country code specified in ISO 3166-1993.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalCurrencyCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the three character currency code specified in ISO 4217-1995.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: CurrencyExchangeRate
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: The rate at which currency can be converted.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDesignAssemblyStatusCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the chronological status of the assembly or board.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDesignRegistrationNotificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the purpose of a design registration notification, e.g. an initial notification or an update.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDesignWinClaimRejectionReasonCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the reason for a design win claim rejection.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDesignWinClaimResponseCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the approval or rejection of a design win claim.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDesignWinClassificationCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDigestAlgorithmCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the Digest Algorithm that has been used to create the message digest. (Should be either "MD5" or "SHA1")

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDocumentFunctionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the function of a document as either a request or a response.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalDocumentTypeCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the type of financial document, e.g. invoice, credit memo or debit memo.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalEngineeringChangeOrderStatusCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the status of an approved engineering change request, that is, an engineering change order.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalEngineeringChangeResponseCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the response to a request for an engineering change.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalEquipmentTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalFeeTypeCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the type of fee being charged.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalFinancePlanIdentifier

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalFinanceTermsCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the terms that govern financing.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalFinancialAdjustmentReasonCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the reason for adjustments to a monetary amount due for payment.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalFinancingRequestActionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the business action requested for financing.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastEventCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the event that initiates a forecast.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastExceptionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying GTIN exception(s).

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastIdentifier
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A unique identifier specifying a specific sales forecast.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastResponseCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying forecast disposition at the GTIN level.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalForecastRevisionReasonCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the reason for a forecast revision or adjustment.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalGeographicRegionCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying a geographic region.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalGovernmentPriorityRatingCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalIncotermsCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalIntervalCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalInvoiceRejectionCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalLanguageCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalLifecycleStatusCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the status that indicates the relative position in the components life cycle.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalLocationIdentifier

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalLotCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalMonetaryAmountTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPartnerRoleClassificationCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPaymentMethodCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPaymentTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPhysicalUnitOfMeasureCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPortOfDeclarationCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPriceProtectionClaimStatusCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPricingTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalPrincipalTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalProductUnitOfMeasureCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalProgramTypeCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalProjectMarketSegmentCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: MonetaryAmount
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Magnitude of currency amount.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: NationalProductCertificationCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Product certification specifying compliance to a National standard.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: NationalPostalCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: QueryConstraint

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: RevisionNumber

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalSpecificationNameCode

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: GlobalSpecificationValueCode
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: Code identifying the name of a value in a technical specification sheet business document. The values are found in a technical dictionary.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: TimeDuration
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A relative period of time specified as a single quantity. The lexical representation for this quantity is the [ISO 8601] representation CCYYMMDDThhmmss.sss, preceded by an optional sign (+ or -), where "CC" represents the number of centuries, "YY" the number of years, "MM" the number of months and "DD" the number of days. The letter "T" is the date/time separator and "hh", "mm", "ss.sss" represent number of hours, minutes and seconds respectively. Note that this representation allows for fractional seconds. For example, to indicate a duration of 1 year, 2 months, 3 days, 10 hours, and 30 minutes, one would write: 00010203T103000.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: TimeStamp
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: An instance in time. Based on the ISO 8601 representation hhmmss.sss where "hh", "mm", "ss.sss" represent hour, minute and second respectively. This representation is followed by a "Z" to indicate Coordinated Universal Time. Informal format: hhmmss.sssZ

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: UniformResourceLocator

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: UniversalResourceIdentifier

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: Value

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: VersionIdentifier
FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.DEFINITION: A unique identifier specifying the version of an entity e.g. a product, a message format, or a standard.

FundamentalBusinessDataEntities.NAME: WireTransferIdentifier
